What To Look For When Selecting A Vendor

Once you've decided on the functionality you want, how do
you choose a  vendor?  Consider:

-      Price
-      Warranty Period
-      Service Policy
-      EPROM Upgrade Policy

Under service policy, for example, determine whether the
vendor will ship a  replacement product (if necessary)
overnight.  Fast response is important  if a printer is
down.

EPROM upgrade policy is also important.  When Banyan
upgrades VINES to a  new version, it may be necessary to
upgrade the software on the EPROM as  well.  There may be
a cost associated with this process depending on the 
vendor.  For example, DPI charges for the EPROM upgrade
(the actual price  has not been set by DPI, but the
amount is expected to be in the $25 to $60  range),
whereas ESI will not charge for the upgrade during the
three year  warranty period. Banyan will not charge VIP
customers for the EPROM  upgrade.

Fortunately, certification is not something you have to
consider. According  to Banyan, there is no certification
or approval process for these types of  products. They
are treated similarly to third party software in this 
respect.

Still Some Shortcomings

A general weakness of all the products is the lack of
management tools that  can diagnose problems with the
printers using these products.  The products  should
support SNMP (Simple Network Management Protocol), the
most common  protocol governing network management and
monitoring of network devices and  their functions.  In
addition, there should be network polling and  inventory
tools that can provide reports on the network printing
devices  and their status. These tools would facilitate
the management process. 
The benefits to connecting printers directly to your
network is clear.  Improved performance and reliability
will result in greater efficiency and  lower network
management costs, as well as the reduced headache
associated  with supporting distributed printers on a
network. The need for flash memory technology as well as
improved management utilities, however, are  desired
courses of direction. 

